Cabinet has approved the Electricity Regulation Amendment Bill and is now open for public comment. Energy sector analyst, Chris Yelland speaks to #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG -Eskom is a step closer to being unbundled. Energy sector analyst Chris Yelland says the Electricity Regulatory Amendment Bill makes this possible. READ: Eskom says employees out of depth In 2019 the President said the utility will be broken up into three companies. They will focus individually on generation, transmission and distribution.